WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.350 --> 00:00:04.496
NULL:  Every gap, every shortcut, every forgotten door -

2
00:00:04.496 --> 00:00:05.765
I will find it.

3
00:00:06.065 --> 00:00:08.212
VEGA:  Not tonight. And the easiest door of all

4
00:00:08.212 --> 00:00:10.145
is a person who hasn't been trained.

5
00:00:10.445 --> 00:00:12.627
NOVA:  So the people are the perimeter too?

6
00:00:12.927 --> 00:00:15.407
VEGA:  The most-attacked one. Let's defend them.

7
00:00:16.457 --> 00:00:20.128
NULL:  Walls and towers? Tedious. People are so much

8
00:00:20.128 --> 00:00:21.352
easier to fool.

9
00:00:21.652 --> 00:00:24.537
VEGA:  Which is why the strongest controls guard the

10
00:00:24.537 --> 00:00:26.012
people, and their data.

11
00:00:27.062 --> 00:00:29.609
VEGA:  Layer three is human. Train them, trust them

12
00:00:29.609 --> 00:00:31.462
carefully, and honor their data.

13
00:00:31.762 --> 00:00:35.380
Three families keep the pact: Awareness & Training,

14
00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:37.650
Personnel Security, and Privacy.

15
00:00:38.700 --> 00:00:41.998
NOVA:  AT, PS, and PT. The teacher, the oathkeeper,

16
00:00:41.998 --> 00:00:43.722
and the privacy herald.

17
00:00:44.772 --> 00:00:47.372
VEGA:  The Drillmaster, Awareness and Training.

18
00:00:47.672 --> 00:00:50.138
VEGA:  A trained citizen spots the trick at the

19
00:00:50.138 --> 00:00:51.432
gate before it opens.

20
00:00:51.732 --> 00:00:54.742
VEGA:  In reality, that's security and privacy training so

21
00:00:54.742 --> 00:00:57.692
people recognize and resist threats like phishing.

22
00:00:58.742 --> 00:01:01.204
NOVA:  What is 'phishing,' exactly?

23
00:01:01.504 --> 00:01:04.155
VEGA:  Bait for people. A message that looks legitimate

24
00:01:04.155 --> 00:01:05.702
but is a trap - and it's how

25
00:01:05.702 --> 00:01:07.304
most breaches actually begin.

26
00:01:08.354 --> 00:01:10.696
NOVA:  How do you stop a perfect phishing email?

27
00:01:10.996 --> 00:01:13.520
VEGA:  You train the human. AT-2 builds that instinct

28
00:01:13.520 --> 00:01:15.715
in everyone - the instinct that hangs up

29
00:01:15.715 --> 00:01:17.636
on the kind of call we opened with.

30
00:01:18.686 --> 00:01:21.686
VEGA:  And AT-3 trains people for their particular role.

31
00:01:25.186 --> 00:01:29.401
ARCHIVIST:  Provide security and privacy literacy training to system

32
00:01:29.401 --> 00:01:34.142
users (including managers, senior executives, and contractors):

33
00:01:35.192 --> 00:01:37.774
VEGA:  The cheapest firewall you own is an alert

34
00:01:37.774 --> 00:01:38.152
human.

35
00:01:43.792 --> 00:01:46.818
VEGA:  The Drillmaster's oath. The sharpest blade is an

36
00:01:46.818 --> 00:01:47.512
alert mind.

37
00:01:48.562 --> 00:01:51.122
VEGA:  The Oathkeeper, Personnel Security.

38
00:01:51.422 --> 00:01:54.397
NULL:  Every guard you hire... could be mine.

39
00:01:54.697 --> 00:01:58.083
VEGA:  In reality, that's screening people, adjusting access when

40
00:01:58.083 --> 00:02:00.885
they move or leave, and guarding against insider

41
00:02:00.885 --> 00:02:01.177
risk.

42
00:02:02.227 --> 00:02:05.507
VEGA:  PS-3 screens people before they're trusted with access.

43
00:02:08.727 --> 00:02:10.469
NOVA:  And when a guard leaves?

44
00:02:10.769 --> 00:02:13.292
VEGA:  PS-4 reclaims the keys, on the way out

45
00:02:13.292 --> 00:02:13.889
the door.

46
00:02:15.227 --> 00:02:18.343
ARCHIVIST:  Upon termination of individual employment:

47
00:02:19.393 --> 00:02:21.854
VEGA:  Access should follow the person, and leave when

48
00:02:21.854 --> 00:02:22.273
they do.

49
00:02:29.693 --> 00:02:32.204
VEGA:  The Oathkeeper's oath. Trust is earned at the

50
00:02:32.204 --> 00:02:33.933
gate, and returned at the door.

51
00:02:34.983 --> 00:02:38.841
VEGA:  The Privacy Herald, P-T, Processing and Transparency of

52
00:02:38.841 --> 00:02:39.823
personal data.

53
00:02:40.123 --> 00:02:43.628
NOVA:  New in Revision 5, privacy now stands beside

54
00:02:43.628 --> 00:02:44.345
security.

55
00:02:44.645 --> 00:02:48.545
VEGA:  In reality, that's processing people's personal data lawfully

56
00:02:48.545 --> 00:02:51.230
and openly - with notice and consent where

57
00:02:51.230 --> 00:02:51.805
required.

58
00:02:52.855 --> 00:02:55.957
NOVA:  P-I-I keeps coming up.

59
00:02:56.257 --> 00:02:59.856
VEGA:  Personally identifiable information - the data that points

60
00:02:59.856 --> 00:03:02.276
to a real human being. Privacy is about

61
00:03:02.276 --> 00:03:04.137
protecting it, and the person.

62
00:03:05.187 --> 00:03:09.367
VEGA:  PT-2 demands a documented authority to process personal

63
00:03:09.367 --> 00:03:09.747
data.

64
00:03:11.687 --> 00:03:14.744
VEGA:  And PT-5 gives people honest notice of how

65
00:03:14.744 --> 00:03:16.127
their data is used.

66
00:03:18.187 --> 00:03:21.673
VEGA:  Authority first, then purpose and notice, then consent

67
00:03:21.673 --> 00:03:24.707
where required, and process only as authorized.

68
00:03:25.007 --> 00:03:28.502
NOVA:  Permission where needed, and honesty, before the data

69
00:03:28.502 --> 00:03:29.029
is used.

70
00:03:30.079 --> 00:03:33.901
ARCHIVIST:  Determine and document the [authority] that permits the

71
00:03:33.901 --> 00:03:37.515
[processing] of personally identifiable information;

72
00:03:38.565 --> 00:03:43.245
VEGA:  Security protects the data. Privacy honors the person.

73
00:03:48.865 --> 00:03:51.541
VEGA:  The Privacy Herald's oath. By what right, for

74
00:03:51.541 --> 00:03:53.385
what purpose, with whose leave?

75
00:03:54.435 --> 00:03:57.146
VEGA:  Not every control is a firewall. Some are

76
00:03:57.146 --> 00:03:59.195
a habit, a contract, a promise.

77
00:04:03.035 --> 00:04:07.001
NOVA:  Scenario: a leaver kept their access. Which guardian

78
00:04:07.001 --> 00:04:08.297
dropped the ball?

79
00:04:15.347 --> 00:04:16.907
VEGA:  The answer is A.

80
00:04:18.947 --> 00:04:21.323
VEGA:  And which guardian is the newcomer to the

81
00:04:21.323 --> 00:04:21.787
catalog?

82
00:04:28.837 --> 00:04:30.437
VEGA:  The answer is C.

83
00:04:32.437 --> 00:04:35.640
NOVA:  Notebook: not every control is a firewall -

84
00:04:35.640 --> 00:04:38.619
some are a habit, a contract, a promise.

85
00:04:38.919 --> 00:04:41.559
VEGA:  People kept, the pact honored.

86
00:04:41.859 --> 00:04:45.374
NULL:  Then I'll strike where no one is even

87
00:04:45.374 --> 00:04:47.274
looking. Your plans.

88
00:04:47.574 --> 00:04:50.014
VEGA:  Then it's time to meet the High Council.
